formatted_address: 417 Fernvale Link, Stall 8 Food Paradise, Singapore 790417
name: Fiery Chicks

reviews.text: It's juz a coffeeshop, so no comment on atmosphere. Food is always good since they opened in this coffeeshop, better than previous & nearby western food places. Their spring chicken especially, is very fresh & juicy! Recommended. Pasta also gd as my family hv tried a few types & all gd. Service wise, we are served by the young man all d time, they'r nice chaps & accept feedbacks too. It's always our first choice. üëç

Ordered chicken Cutlet for $7.90. Food was ready pretty quickly and the cutlet taste good. But the portion is a tad smaller than what I get from other Western Food stalls around Sengkang area.

Rooms for improvement.

Came with my wife and bought the chicken cutlet, upon paying the female cashier (not local, viet) gave me this rude attitude like I did something to offend her. I asked her whats wrong and she pretends to smile. When collecting my food, she rolled her eyes at me. Food was soso, price was expensive, highly NOT recommended with this kind of staff attitude. Ask her to go back if she is not happy to work
Use fresh chicken for the spring chicken, hence meat quite juicy.

If theres an option for zero stars i would give. Vietnamese cashier thinks everybody offended her, gave blackface for absolutely no reason and super rude. No manners at all, please save you money and do not come here to eat
